Senate State and Local Government 1
Amendment No. 1 to SB2226
Briggs
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 2226* House Bill No. 2538
by deleting all language after the enacting clause and substituting:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 64-9-104(a), is amended by adding
the following as a new subdivision:
( ) Issue bonds in the manner provided by title 7, chapter 53 for the sole
purpose of financing, in whole or in part, the cost of the acquisition, purchase,
construction, reconstruction, improvement, betterment, or extension of the water system
or wastewater system operated by the authority. The board, in determining the cost,
may include all costs and estimated costs of the issuance of the bonds, all engineering,
inspection, fiscal and legal expenses, if related to the issuance of the bonds, and interest
that is estimated to accrue during the construction period and six (6) months thereafter
on money borrowed or that is estimated to be borrowed pursuant to this chapter. The
state is not liable on bonds of the authority, the bonds are not a debt of this state, and
the bonds must contain on the face of the bonds a statement to that effect. In addition to
approval by the board, the issuance of bonds for purposes under this subdivision (a)( )
is subject to the approval of the state funding board established in § 9-9-101.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect upon becoming law, the public welfare requiring it.
